cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CR

This paper is about generating white-box adversarial examples for text classification using a neural classifier. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the method, which suggests that it could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a method that relies on gradients, which could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of constraints, which could relate to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
